HEADWORD: Bubale
<hw>Bu"ba*le</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>bubale</ets>. See <er>Buffalo</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large antelope (<spn>Alcelaphus bubalis</spn>)
of Egypt and the Desert of Sahara, supposed by some to be the fallow
deer of the Bible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

